<BaseLayout title="Python Performance Optimization · CS Notebook">
  <article class="space-y-6">
    <header>
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-primary-cyan mb-2">Languages / Python Performance</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">
        <Bilingual><span slot="zh">性能优化</span><span slot="en">Performance Optimization</span></Bilingual>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
        <Bilingual>
          <span slot="zh">Python 在国内游戏圈大量用于<b>脚本层</b>——热更新逻辑、配置解析、测试工具、服务端业务（Panda3D/BigWorld 架构）。但前面两页揭示了它的结构性代价：每对象 16B 头、引用计数分摊进每条指令、动态类型分发、GIL 单线程。本页从<b>内存</b>和 <b>CPU</b> 两条线讲实战优化，并重点剖析 <code>dict</code>——游戏脚本里最常用的结构——该如何压榨。点击下方对比 Python 与 C/C++ 的内存代价。</span>
          <span slot="en">Python is widely used in China's game industry as a <b>scripting layer</b> — hot-update logic, config parsing, test tooling, server business logic (Panda3D/BigWorld). But the previous two pages revealed its structural costs: 16B per-object header, refcounting smeared across every instruction, dynamic type dispatch, single-threaded GIL. This page covers practical optimization along <b>memory</b> and <b>CPU</b> axes, with a deep dive on <code>dict</code> — the most used structure in game scripts — and how to squeeze it. Click below to compare Python vs C/C++ memory costs.</span>
        </Bilingual>
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- 交互：内存占用对比 -->
    <div class="glass p-5" data-viz="mem-compare">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <button class="btn mc-btn btn-primary" data-case="int"><span data-lang="zh">整数</span><span data-lang="en">int</span></button>
        <button class="btn mc-btn" data-case="struct"><span data-lang="zh">实体对象</span><span data-lang="en">entity</span></button>
        <button class="btn mc-btn" data-case="array"><span data-lang="zh">10万元素数组</span><span data-lang="en">100k array</span></button>
      </div>
      <svg id="mc-svg" viewBox="0 0 800 260" class="w-full h-64 viz-stage"></svg>
    </div>

    <!-- 为什么 Python 占内存 -->
    <section class="glass p-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-3"><Bilingual><span slot="zh">为什么 Python 这么占内存</span><span slot="en">Why Python Eats So Much Memory</span></Bilingual></h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
        <Bilingual>
          <span slot="zh">Python 内存膨胀有三个叠加原因：<br>
          • <b class="text-func-amber">对象头税</b>：每个对象固定 16-24B 头部，存 1000 个 int 要 28KB，C 只要 4KB。<br>
          • <b class="text-primary-cyan">一切堆分配</b>：Python 对象<b>只能在堆上</b>（没有栈对象概念），连循环里的临时 int 都要 malloc 一次——而 C++ 的 <code>int i</code> 在栈上零开销。<br>
          • <b class="text-func-green">容器间接</b>：<code>list</code> 存的是<b>指针数组</b>而非值本身——<code>[1,2,3]</code> 是 3 个 int 对象(28B×3) + 3 个指针(8B×3) + list 头(56B) = 170B，而 C++ <code>vector&lt;int&gt;{1,2,3}</code> 仅 12B 数据。<br>
          这就是"Python 占内存通常是 C++ 的 5-10 倍"的根源。</span>
          <span slot="en">Python's memory bloat has three compounding causes:<br>
          • <b class="text-func-amber">Object header tax</b>: 16-24B fixed header per object — 1000 ints cost 28KB vs C's 4KB.<br>
          • <b class="text-primary-cyan">All-heap allocation</b>: Python objects <b>only live on the heap</b> (no stack objects) — even a loop's temporary int gets a malloc, while C++'s <code>int i</code> is zero-cost on stack.<br>
          • <b class="text-func-green">Container indirection</b>: <code>list</code> stores an array of <b>pointers</b>, not values — <code>[1,2,3]</code> = 3 int objects (28B×3) + 3 pointers (8B×3) + list header (56B) = 170B, vs C++ <code>vector&lt;int&gt;{1,2,3}</code>'s 12B of data.<br>
          This is the root of "Python uses 5-10x the memory of C++".</span>
        </Bilingual>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- 内存优化 -->
    <section class="glass p-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-3"><Bilingual><span slot="zh">内存优化：__slots__ / intern / 对象池</span><span slot="en">Memory: __slots__ / intern / Object Pool</span></Bilingual></h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mb-3"><Bilingual><span slot="zh">压低 Python 内存有四板斧：<b>__slots__</b> 关掉每个实例的 <code>__dict__</code>（省 ~100B/实例）；<b>intern</b> 复用相同字符串/小整数；<b>对象池</b>复用高频短命对象（如游戏里的 vec3/bullet）；<b>numpy / array</b> 把同质数据压成连续 C 数组（绕过对象模型）。前三者是"省头部"，后者是"绕过模型"——对大批量数值数据，<b>numpy 是唯一正解</b>。</span><span slot="en">Four levers to cut Python memory: <b>__slots__</b> disables per-instance <code>__dict__</code> (saves ~100B/instance); <b>intern</b> reuses identical strings/small ints; <b>object pools</b> reuse high-frequency short-lived objects (e.g. game vec3/bullet); <b>numpy / array</b> packs homogeneous data into contiguous C arrays (bypassing the object model). The first three "save headers"; the last "bypasses the model" — for large-scale numeric data, <b>numpy is the only right answer</b>.</span></Bilingual></p>
      <CodeTabs
  cpp={`<pre><code>// C++ 对照：这些优化在 C++ 里"天然存在"
// C++ 对象默认无运行时头，字段紧凑排列，可栈分配

struct Vec3 &#123;            // 紧凑 12 字节（或 alignas 后 16）
    float x, y, z;
&#125;;

// 大批量数据：连续内存，缓存友好
std::vector&lt;Vec3&gt; particles(100000);
// 100000 * 12 = 1.2MB，全部连续，SIMD 友好

// 对象池：固定大小块复用
class ParticlePool &#123;
    std::vector&lt;Particle&gt; pool;
    std::vector&lt;size_t&gt; freeList;
public:
    Particle* alloc() &#123;
        if (freeList.empty()) &#123; pool.emplace_back(); return &amp;pool.back(); &#125;
        auto p = &amp;pool[freeList.back()]; freeList.pop_back();
        return p;
    &#125;
    void free(Particle* p) &#123; freeList.push_back(p - pool.data()); &#125;
&#125;;

// C++ 不需要 __slots__：struct 本就没有虚字典
// C++ 不需要 intern：字符串字面量自动去重（链接器）
// C++ 不需要 numpy：原生数组就是连续内存</code></pre>`}
  py={`<pre><code>import sys

# ===== 1. __slots__: 关掉实例 __dict__ =====
class EntityDict:           # 默认有 __dict__
    def __init__(self): self.x, self.y, self.hp = 0, 0, 100

class EntitySlots:          # __slots__ 固定字段
    __slots__ = ('x', 'y', 'hp')
    def __init__(self): self.x, self.y, self.hp = 0, 0, 100

e1 = EntityDict(); e2 = EntitySlots()
print(sys.getsizeof(e1) + sys.getsizeof(e1.__dict__))  # ~152
print(sys.getsizeof(e2))                                 # ~56  省 ~63%!
# 代价：不能动态加属性（也是优点：防拼写错误）

# ===== 2. intern: 复用相同字符串 =====
a = sys.intern("player_damage_" + "fire")
b = sys.intern("player_damage_" + "fire")
print(a is b)  # True —— 同一对象，省内存 + 比较变指针比较 O(1)
# CPython 自动 intern: 看似标识符的字符串、-5~256 的 int

# ===== 3. 对象池: 复用高频短命对象 =====
class Bullet:
    __slots__ = ('x', 'y', 'vx', 'vy', 'alive')
    def reset(self, x, y, vx, vy):
        self.x, self.y, self.vx, self.vy = x, y, vx, vy
        self.alive = True

class BulletPool:
    def __init__(self, n):
        self.pool = [Bullet() for _ in range(n)]  # 预分配
        self.free = list(self.pool)
    def spawn(self, x, y, vx, vy):
        b = self.free.pop() if self.free else Bullet()
        b.reset(x, y, vx, vy); return b
    def reclaim(self, b): self.free.append(b)  # 复用，不 GC
# 每帧创建/回收数百子弹 → 0 次 malloc

# ===== 4. numpy: 绕过对象模型 =====
import numpy as np
# 10万粒子，用 Python list 存对象:
class P:
    __slots__=('x','y','z')
ps_list = [P() for _ in range(100000)]   # ~4.8MB (100000*48)
# 用 numpy:
arr = np.zeros((100000, 3), dtype=np.float32)  # 1.2MB!  连续内存
# 4 倍省内存 + SIMD 加速 + 缓存友好</code></pre>`}
      />
    </section>

    <!-- CPU 优化 -->
    <section class="glass p-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-3"><Bilingual><span slot="zh">CPU 优化：GIL、向量化、C 扩展、多进程</span><span slot="en">CPU: GIL, Vectorization, C Extensions, Multiprocessing</span></Bilingual></h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mb-3"><Bilingual><span slot="zh">Python 慢的 CPU 侧原因：<b>每条字节码都过 VM 大循环</b>（见虚拟机页）、<b>动态类型分发</b>（<code>+</code> 要查 <code>tp_add</code>）、<b>GIL</b> 阻止多核并行。优化路径按收益排序：<b>算法优先</b>（O(n²)→O(n log n) 胜过一切微优化）→ <b>向量化</b>（numpy 把循环下沉到 C）→ <b>C 扩展/Cython</b>（热点编译）→ <b>多进程</b>（绕 GIL 用多核）→ <b>PyPy/JIT</b>（换运行时）。<b>多线程对 CPU 密集任务无效</b>（GIL），只对 I/O 有用。</span><span slot="en">Python's CPU slowness: <b>each bytecode through the VM loop</b> (see VM page), <b>dynamic type dispatch</b> (<code>+</code> looks up <code>tp_add</code>), <b>GIL</b> blocking multicore parallelism. Optimization by ROI: <b>algorithm first</b> (O(n²)→O(n log n) beats any micro-opt) → <b>vectorization</b> (numpy sinks loops to C) → <b>C extensions/Cython</b> (compile hotspots) → <b>multiprocessing</b> (use multicore around GIL) → <b>PyPy/JIT</b> (swap runtime). <b>Threading is useless for CPU-bound</b> (GIL); only helps I/O.</span></Bilingual></p>
      <pre class="glass p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="text-func-green"># GIL：全局解释器锁</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted"># 同一时刻只有一个线程执行字节码 → 多线程无法利用多核做 CPU 计算</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted"># GIL 在 ceval.c 循环边界定期释放（每 ~100 条指令或 I/O 时）</span>

<span class="text-primary-cyan"># 1. 向量化：把 Python 循环下沉到 numpy 的 C 循环</span>
import numpy as np
arr = np.random.rand(10_000_000)

<span class="text-func-red"># 慢：Python 层逐元素循环（每步过 VM + 类型分发）</span>
result = sum(x * 2 for x in arr)          <span class="text-ink-muted"># ~1.2s</span>

<span class="text-func-green"># 快：numpy 向量化（一次 C 层批量操作）</span>
result = (arr * 2).sum()                    <span class="text-ink-muted"># ~15ms  80倍!</span>

<span class="text-primary-cyan"># 2. C 扩展 / Cython：把热点函数编译成 C</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  纯 Python:</span>
def mandel(c, max_iter):
    z = 0
    for n in range(max_iter):
        if abs(z) &gt; 2: return n
        z = z*z + c
    return max_iter
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  Cython (加类型注解后编译):</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  cdef double z=0; cdef int n  → 接近 C 速度，无 VM 开销</span>

<span class="text-primary-cyan"># 3. 多进程绕 GIL（每个进程独立 GIL）</span>
from multiprocessing import Pool
def work(x): return x * x
with Pool(8) as p:           <span class="text-ink-muted"># 真·8核并行</span>
    results = p.map(work, range(10**6))
<span class="text-ink-muted"># 代价：进程间内存不共享，数据要序列化(pickle)传输 → 仅适合粗粒度任务</span>

<span class="text-primary-cyan"># 4. I/O 密集用 asyncio / 线程（GIL 在 I/O 时释放）</span>
import asyncio
async def fetch(url): ...    <span class="text-ink-muted"># 单线程并发，无 GIL 争用</span>

<span class="text-func-amber"># 选型决策树:</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  算法能优化?           → 先优化算法</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  数值批量计算?         → numpy 向量化</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  单函数热点?           → Cython / numba @jit</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  多核 CPU 密集?        → multiprocessing</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  I/O 密集?            → asyncio / threading</span>
<span class="text-ink-muted">#  整体慢?              → 考虑 PyPy (JIT)</span></code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- dict 优化与游戏开发 -->
    <section class="glass p-5">
      <h2 class="font-semibold mb-3"><Bilingual><span slot="zh">dict 优化与游戏脚本实践</span><span slot="en">dict Optimization & Game Script Practices</span></Bilingual></h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mb-3"><Bilingual><span slot="zh"><code>dict</code> 是 Python 脚本里<b>最高频</b>的结构——存配置表、实体属性、消息映射、缓存。Python 3.6+ 的<b>紧凑 dict</b> 已比旧版省 20-25%：它把键值对存进一个紧凑 <code>entries</code> 数组（插入有序），另用一个稀疏<b>索引数组</b>做哈希查找——这样 entries 连续、缓存友好，且删除留下空洞只影响索引。进一步优化：<b>共享 key dict</b>（同类的多个实例共享 key 数组，只存各自的 value）、<b>预知大小避免 rehash</b>、以及<b>用 dataclass(slots=True) / namedtuple 替代属性 dict</b>。游戏脚本中要警惕"用 dict 存上万个实体属性"——那会让缓存雪崩。</span><span slot="en"><code>dict</code> is the <b>most frequent</b> structure in Python scripts — config tables, entity attributes, message maps, caches. Python 3.6+'s <b>compact dict</b> already saves 20-25% vs legacy: it stores key-value pairs in a compact <code>entries</code> array (insertion-ordered), with a separate sparse <b>index array</b> for hash lookup — making entries contiguous & cache-friendly, with deletion holes only affecting the index. Further: <b>shared-key dict</b> (same-class instances share the key array, only values differ), <b>pre-sizing to avoid rehash</b>, and <b>dataclass(slots=True)/namedtuple instead of attribute dicts</b>. In game scripts, beware "storing tens of thousands of entity attributes in dicts" — that triggers cache thrashing.</span></Bilingual></p>
      <CodeTabs
  cpp={`<pre><code>// C++ 对照：游戏引擎几乎不用 unordered_map 存实体属性
// 而是用 SoA（Structure of Arrays）连续存储

// DoA（Array of Structures）：缓存不友好
struct Entity &#123; float x,y,z; int hp; &#125;;
std::vector&lt;Entity&gt; entities;   // 遍历 x 时跳过 hp，cache miss

// SoA（Structure of Arrays）：缓存友好，SIMD 友好
struct Entities &#123;
    std::vector&lt;float&gt; x, y, z;  // 连续
    std::vector&lt;int&gt;   hp;       // 单独连续
&#125;;
// 遍历所有 x → 完美缓存命中，可向量化

// 这就是为什么 C++ 引擎能跑几十万实体而 Python 脚本卡在几千
// Python dict 本质是 DoA 的极端版：每个属性都是独立的堆对象 + 指针跳转</code></pre>`}
  py={`<pre><code>import sys
from dataclasses import dataclass

# ===== 紧凑 dict 原理（3.6+）=====
# 旧版 dict: 每个槽存 (hash, key, value)，稀疏，空洞浪费
# 新版 dict: entries[] 紧凑存 (hash,key,value) + indices[] 稀疏索引
d = &#123;'hp': 100, 'mp': 50, 'name': 'hero'&#125;
# entries = [(hash,'hp',100),(hash,'mp',50),(hash,'name','hero')]  连续!
# indices = [0, None, 1, None, 2, ...]  稀疏(按 hash 取模定位)
# 优势: 插入有序、entries 连续缓存友好、省内存

# ===== 共享 key dict: 同类实例共享 key 数组 =====
class Player:
    def __init__(self):
        self.hp = 100; self.mp = 50; self.name = ""  # 触发实例 dict
p1, p2, p3 = Player(), Player(), Player()
# 三个实例的 __dict__ 共享同一个 keys 数组，只各自存 value 数组
# 省: N 个实例只需 1 份 key 存储（但每个仍有 dict 头开销）

# ===== 游戏脚本: 别用 dict 存大量实体 =====
<span class="text-func-red"># 反例: 10万实体 × 5 属性 = 50万个 dict entry</span>
entities = [&#123;'x':0,'y':0,'z':0,'hp':100,'type':'mob'&#125;
            for _ in range(100000)]
# 内存: ~100000 * 232B(dict头+entries) ≈ 23MB，且全是堆对象，缓存雪崩

<span class="text-func-green"># 正解: dataclass(slots=True) + numpy 批量属性</span>
@dataclass(slots=True)
class Entity:
    x: float; y: float; z: float; hp: int; type_id: int

import numpy as np
class World:
    def __init__(self, n):
        self.pos = np.zeros((n, 3), np.float32)   # 连续 12n 字节
        self.hp = np.full(n, 100, np.int32)        # 连续 4n 字节
        self.type_id = np.zeros(n, np.int8)        # 连续 n 字节
# 10万实体: 1.2MB + 0.4MB + 0.1MB ≈ 1.7MB，且遍历 pos 走 SIMD
# 比 dict 方案省 13 倍内存 + 快 50 倍以上

# ===== dict 使用最佳实践 =====
# 1. 配置表/消息映射: dict 是合适的（量小、查表频繁）
ACTIONS = &#123;'attack': do_attack, 'defend': do_defend&#125;
# 2. 预知大小: dict.fromkeys 一次性建好，避免反复 rehash
lookup = dict.fromkeys(keys, default)   # 一次性分配
# 3. 查表用 set 而非 list: in 操作 O(1) vs O(n)
valid = &#123;'sword', 'bow', 'staff'&#125;  # if item in valid: O(1)
# 4. 大量属性 → dataclass(slots=True)；批量数值 → numpy</code></pre>`}
      />
      <p class="text-xs text-ink-muted mt-3"><Bilingual><span slot="zh">关联阅读：<a class="text-primary-cyan underline" href="/topics/py-vm">虚拟机与字节码</a>解释为何每条指令都慢；<a class="text-primary-cyan underline" href="/topics/py-objects">对象模型与内存</a>解释为何每个对象都大；<a class="text-primary-cyan underline" href="/topics/cpp-memory">C++ 内存管理</a>对比栈堆与缓存友好的 SoA 设计。</span><span slot="en">Related: <a class="text-primary-cyan underline" href="/topics/py-vm">VM & Bytecode</a> for why each instruction is slow; <a class="text-primary-cyan underline" href="/topics/py-objects">Object Model & Memory</a> for why each object is large; <a class="text-primary-cyan underline" href="/topics/cpp-memory">C++ Memory</a> for stack/heap & cache-friendly SoA design.</span></Bilingual></p>
    </section>
